<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepali King Meets With China's PLA Head </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Nepali King Birendra met here
Monday with Fu Quanyou, chief of the General Staff of the People's
Liberation Army (PLA) of China.
</P>
<P>
King Birendra told Fu that he hoped the military ties between
Nepal and China will be further strengthened in the future.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed thanks for China's support for Nepal's
struggle for independence and economic development.
</P>
<P>
"Although China is much larger than Nepal, China showed
understanding and support to Nepal's struggle for independence and
sovereignty and has extended much assistance to Nepal's economic
development," the king said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the wish that China will achieve sustained
development and prosperity in order to make greater contributions
to world peace.
</P>
<P>
Fu said China and Nepal are two close neighbors whose
friendship can be dated back to more than 1,000 years ago.
</P>
<P>
"As close neighbors, we don't have any outstanding problems,"
he noted."This has provided a solid basis for economic cooperation
between our two countries."
</P>
<P>
The PLA head expressed sincere thanks for Nepal's support to
China on issues relating to human rights, Taiwan and Tibet.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that Nepal will further support China in this regard,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
Fu will conclude his six-day official visit to Nepal Tuesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
