<HEADLINE> 19 Killed in Indian Bus Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- At least 19 people, including
six women, were killed and 33 injured in a collision between a bus
and a sand-laden lorry on a busy highway in Kanchipuram district
of South India's Tamil Nadu Monday, the Press Trust of India
reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred on the narrow Thapalmedu bridge in
Padalam in the district, police were quoted as saying. 16 victims
died on the spot while three succumbed to injuries in hospital.
</P>
<P>
The state-owned bus was going to Madras from Cuddalore while
the lorry was proceeding to Maduranthakam in the same district
when the mishap occurred, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
