<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Macedonia Hope for More Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 10 (Xinhua) -- With three agreements signed here
Monday, the Ukrainian and Macedonian governments expressed their
content with the current bilateral economic ties and hoped for
more cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The agreements, on consular contacts, cooperation in legal
procedure of civil and criminal cases and cooperation in tourist
business, were signed following meetings of visiting Macedonian
Premier Ljupco Georgievski with Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma
and with Prime Minister Viktor Yushchenko.
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation and trade between Ukraine and Macedonia
have been active in recent years, Yushchenko told a new conference
after meeting with his Macedonian counterpart.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the potential in military cooperation and
for working with Macedonia to develop the Europe-Asia corridor.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Georgievsk told reporters that he is optimistic
about reaching a free trade agreement between these two neighbors,
which is expected to be signed in June.
</P>
<P>
Leading a delegation of many entrepreneurs, Georgievski arrived
here Sunday night. He will leave on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
