<HEADLINE> Olympic Champion Xiong Ni Claims Chinese National Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Olympic diving champion Xiong Ni
led all the way to clinch the men's 3-meter springboard title at
the Chinese national diving championships here on Monday, the
tournament also served as the domestic trails for the Sydney
Olympic Games in the September.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old Xiong collected a total winning points of 751.
40 by dominating the competition since the semi-final. His fourth
dive in the final gave scored day's highest of 91.80 points.
</P>
<P>
Xiao Hailiang, who survived a minor mistake for his last
routine, won the silver medal with a 727.80, outpointing Yu
Zhuocheng, Atlanta Olympic runner-up, to the third place in 726.
85.
</P>
<P>
Xiong, who retired in 1997 and resumed training one year ago,
had shown his strong comeback on his road to Sydney Olympics with
stardom.
</P>
<P>
"I am satisfied with today's high scores. I hope I can reach my
peak form in Sydney," Xiong said.
</P>
<P>
According to the Chinese Swimming Association (CSA), top two
divers in each event with best results in three out of the five
trails could make the Olympic line-ups.
</P>
<P>
With three wins in the four trails, Xiong had already qualified
for the Sydney Olympics in the men's springboard, while another
qualifier is yet to decided. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
