<DOCNO> XIE20000411.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Danish Modern Design Art Show Opens in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 10 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of modern
architecture and design art of Denmark opened today in Guangzhou,
capital of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, entitled "the Danish Wave", commemorates the
50th anniversary of diplomatic ties between Denmark and China.
</P>
<P>
On display are more than 70 pieces highlighting Denmark's
contemporary construction styles and designing arts.
</P>
<P>
The show is jointly sponsored by the Chinese Ministry of
Culture and the Danish Embassy in China. Danish Ambassador to
China Christopher Bo Bramsen, and Tom Jensen, Danish Counsul
General in Guangzhou, attended today's opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will run in Guangzhou for 15 days, and will be
moved to the Shanghai Library in May and the Revolutionary Museum
in Beijing in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
