<BODY>
<HEADLINE> TV Film On Drug Control Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- An educational film for TV,
titled "Narcotics Control Regulations in China", is ready for
broadcast, the Ministry of Public Security announced today.
</P>
<P>
The 106-minute-long film provides detailed explanations of the
drug-related regulations included in China's Criminal Law, the
Compulsory Drug Rehabilitation Regulation issued by the State
Council, and certain managerial regulations on anesthetic
medicines and medicines for mental patients, which were issued by
the Ministry of Health.
</P>
<P>
The film also includes interviews with drug dealers and addicts.
</P>
<P>
Deng Ming, an official with the Ministry of Public Security,
said that the film could be used as a textbook for both law
enforcers and the public. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
