<DOCNO> XIE20000411.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BU Establishes High-Tech Park in Xinjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- China's prestigious Beijing
University (BU) will establish a high-tech park in the Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region in the northwest this May, in a bid to
promote the local economy of the area.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Urumqi Economic Development Zone in this
capital of Xinjiang said today that the 33.3-hectare park will
include research facilities for projects involving microbe
fertilizer, wind power usage, and bio-plastic sheeting.
</P>
<P>
The zone, established in 1994, is the only state level economic
development zone among China's five northwest provinces and
autonomous regions (Xinjiang, Ningxia, Inner Mongolia, Shaanxi and
Gansu).
</P>
<P>
It has attracted over five billion yuan of investment and 903
enterprises since it was formed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
