<HEADLINE> Shanghai Holds Animal Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The fourth Shanghai Animal
Festival opened here today, with "Loving Peace, Protecting the
Environment, and Caring for Animals" as its theme.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Zoo will present over 6,000 rare animals from 600
species during the two-month festival period. The zoo disclosed
that for the first time, it will show to the public a couple of
white tigers.
</P>
<P>
The zoo also invited a circus from Kazakhstan and a kite
performance troupe from east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The festival attracted an average of 500,000 tourists every
time since it debuted in 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
