<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wholesale Market Fire Injures Three in Kunming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A fire broke out in a wholesale
market in this capital city of Southwest China's Yunnan Province
this afternoon and burned for seven hours.
</P>
<P>
Four people were injured in the fire, including a fire fighter
who was listed in stable condition by press time.
</P>
<P>
The fire destroyed the Nanyao Cosmopolitan Wholesale Market and
four adjacent residential buildings, involving an area of about 10,
000 square meters. It is the most serious fire in this city in
recent history.
</P>
<P>
The marketplace near Kunming Railway Station sells mainly
clothes, electrical appliances and toys.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out at 5:12 PM today in a storage shed and
quickly spread to the whole market because of strong wind.
</P>
<P>
Dealers and nearby residents were quickly evacuated from the
area, and no deaths have been reported.  
</P>
</TEXT>
