<HEADLINE> Arab League Warns Israel Against More Attacks in Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Arab League Secretary General Esmat
Abdel-Meguid warned Tuesday against an escalation of Israeli
military campaign in south Lebanon, saying that the Jewish state's
policies would lead to the "destruction of peace."
</P>
<P>
Israeli aircraft carried out four raids Tuesday on the area
occupied by Israel in south Lebanon in retaliation for the
Hezbollah guerrillas' rocket attacks on Israeli army positions.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid warned of the "dangers of the continuation of
Israeli policy," which he said was "leading towards the destruction
of peace," in remarks to reporters after meeting Russian Ambassador
to Egypt Vladimir Gudev.
</P>
<P>
He also accused Israel of obstructing peace negotiations with
the Palestinians and Syrians as well as the Lebanese and said
Jewish settlement building in the West Bank has increased under the
government of Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak.
</P>
<P>
The Arab League chief called on Russia to use its weight as co-
sponsor of the peace process to convince Israel to reverse its
hostile policies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
