<HEADLINE> Nigeria's FM Pledges to Improve G-77's Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Foreign Minister Alhaji
Sule Lamido pledged Tuesday that the Group of 77 countries would
improve its work mechanisms with the aim to make the South Summit'
s agreements be as effective as possible.
</P>
<P>
The speaker obtained financial support from all the
participants to back up the work of the group's president in New
York regarding the implementation of the summit's final
declaration and the follow-up to the action programs originated at
this meeting.
</P>
<P>
Sule Lamido, whose country is actually heading the G-77, read
the opening speech at the foreign ministers' meeting, preceding
the South Summit which is to begin its work Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
During his speech before the delegations gathered at the
Convention Palace in Havana, he expressed confidence that the
final documents would improve the unity and contribute to
communication aiming at the international community's development.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the internal performance of the G-77, he said that up
to now there have been many futile attempts directed at creating
an effective mechanism to drive the fulfillment of the adopted
accords from former summits.
</P>
<P>
In this sense he reminded that nowadays there is only a reduced
personnel at New York city's office, which mainly depends on the
funding provided by the country selected to head in a given year
the Group of 77.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian foreign minister proposed that prior to the end of
the South Summit, on Friday, the 133 countries that make up the
organization make a commitment to improve the funding to finance
the work of the New York headquarters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
