<HEADLINE> Venezuelan President To Attend G-77 Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan President Hugo Chavez
is departing Tuesday to Havana to attend the Summit of the Group
of 77 on April 12-14, the Foreign Ministry said .
</P>
<P>
The president is scheduled to meet in Havana with his 15
counterparts from developing nations. On Tuesday's evening he will
meet with Palestine's leader Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he will meet with the leaders of Algeria, Nigeria,
South Africa, Indonesia, Malaysia, Vietnam, the Dominican Republic,
Grenada, Guyana, Haiti, Jamaica, Qatar and Trinidad and Tobago,
among others, said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela will not present any particular project to the summit,
but will support the final declaration which is aimed to improve
the South-South, and North-South relations, according to the
source. 
