<HEADLINE> Greek Communists Protest Against U.S. Troops From Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Members of Greece's Communist
Party (KKE) Tuesday protested at a northern Greek port against a U.
S. military contingent returning from the recent military exercise
in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
When KKE members attempted to block a military convoy of 80
vehicles carrying 586 U.S. troops heading south to the small port
of Gritsa, south of Thessaloniki, scuffles took place between
protesters and police, and two KKE protesters and one police
officer were reportedly injured, according to the semi-official
Athens News Agency (ANA).
</P>
<P>
KKE officials accused the police of attacking the protesters
without provocation.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. troops disembarked from the port aboard U.S. Navy
Hovercrafts before boarding three tank carriers vessels anchored
offshore.
</P>
<P>
Last month, the KKE organized similar protests against U.S.
troops when they passed through the northern Greek port of
Thessaloniki on their way to Kosovo to participate in the military
exercise, codenamed "Dynamic Response." 
