<HEADLINE> CA Delivers Roadmaps for Newly Acquired Sterling Software Product Lines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW ORLEANS, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Computer Associates
International, Inc (CA) Tuesday issued roadmaps for its recently
acquired Sterling Software, Inc (Sterling) products.
</P>
<P>
These roadmaps outline how CA plans to extend its global
leadership in the delivery of software and services to enable
faster, better, safer and more reliable eBusiness computing.
</P>
<P>
Announced at CA-World 2000 held in New Orleans in Louisiana,
the United States, the roadmaps outline CA's aggressive plans to
extend Sterling products through ongoing development and
integration with CA software to deliver the industry's most
extensive range of eBusiness solutions.
</P>
<P>
The roadmaps cover CA's plans for enhancing, extending and
integrating Sterling technologies in the following important areas:
</P>
<P>
-- eBusiness Intelligence. CA will integrate the Sterling
EUREKA product family as an essential component of its eBusiness
solutions;
</P>
<P>
-- Application Development. CA will continue to support and
extend the Sterling COOL family of application development and
modeling products along with its Jasmine intelligence eBusiness
platform;
</P>
<P>
-- Storage Management. CA's acquisition of Sterling Software
extends CA's industry leadership in storage management technology;
</P>
<P>
-- Network Management. The addition of Sterling's OS/390
network management solution will further enhance CA's ability to
manage the eBusiness infrastructure;
</P>
<P>
-- Automation. CA will extend sterling's SOLVE: Operations
family of products with Sysplex-enablement and the capability to
automate actions for new workload and eBusiness applications;
</P>
<P>
-- Help Desk. CA will leverage Sterling's SOLVE: Central Help
Desk technology through integration with its Service Desk product
line.
</P>
<P>
CA, the world's leading business software company, delivers
the end-to-end infrastructure to enable eBusiness through
innovative technology, services and education.
</P>
<P>
CA has 18,000 employees worldwide and had revenue of 6.3
billion U.S. dollars for the year ended December 31, 1999.
</P>
</TEXT>
