made to France by an Algerian head of state after President Chadli
Bendjedid in November 1983.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Algeria and France are closely woven but
highly sensitive nearly 40 years after Algeria won its
independence from France.
</P>
<P>
France was accused by Algeria of trying to interfere into its
internal affairs when the north African country went through a
bloody civil conflict starting from 1992.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two countries have been improving after
Bouteflika came to power one year ago. 
