<HEADLINE> Meningitis Curbed in Parts of Ethiopia: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia has curbed the
meningitis epidemic that surfaced in the states of Amharic, Tigray
and Gambella, the Ethiopian News Agency quoted a Health Ministry
official as saying Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Vaccination services were provided to more than 80,000 people
in the affected areas, epidemic disease expert Belay Teklu said.
</P>
<P>
According to Belay, 14 out of 221 people who got the infections
have died of meningitis.
</P>
<P>
"The number of meningitis victims could have been much bigger
had it not been for the preventive measures timely taken," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Despite of medicines supplied to the affected areas, the expert
warned that it might be possible for another pandemic disease
because of the unusually prolonged dry weather conducive for the
spread of the disease.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is said to have fallen geographically in the
african-meningitis belt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
