<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 11 (Xinhua) -- South Africa remains the
most popular emerging market among fund managers, said a monthly
Merrill Lynch Fund Manager Survey released on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The latest survey showed that 52 percent of the managers polled
favor South Africa, followed by Asia (29 percent) and Latin
America (19 percent).
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, all fund managers surveyed agreed
that the domestic economy in South Africa will get stronger over
the next 12 months.
</P>
<P>
Some 58 percent of them have "high" confidence that the country
is following the correct macroeconomic policies while no fund
manager has "low confidence", the survey said. 
