<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai King Approves New Cabinet List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 11 (Xinhua) -- King Bhumibol Adulyadej of
Thailand Tuesday approved the new cabinet list submitted by Prime
Minister Chuan Leekpai, according to local radio reports.
</P>
<P>
Six cabinet seats were changed during the government reshuffle.
</P>
<P>
Banyat Bantadtan, deputy leader of the ruling Democrat Party,
was named as deputy prime minister and interior minister to
replace Sanan Kachornprasart, who resigned earlier this month
after being accused of falsifying his assets and liabilities
records.
</P>
<P>
The other cabinet shifts were made within another ruling party,
Chart Thai.
</P>
<P>
Viroj Pao-in, a parliament representative of Chart Thai,
replaced Panja Kesornthong as deputy prime minister who had
resigned due to health problems.
</P>
<P>
Pongpol Adireksarn, the party's secretary-general, was ousted
from the cabinet as agriculture and cooperatives minister because
of soured relationship with party leader Banharn Silpa-Archa.
</P>
<P>
Pongpol's post was taken over by Praphat Phothisuthon, a deputy
interior minister, whose job was taken over by Sonthaya Khunpluem,
a deputy transport and communications minister.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Labor Minister Jongchai Thiangtham was moved to Sonthaya
's job at the Transport and Communications Ministry while his job
was taken over by Prayuth Siripanich, a Chart Thai parliamentary
representative.
</P>
<P>
Chart Thai leader Banharn had said earlier that his party had
resolved not to make cabinet changes as the government's term had
only a short time left.
</P>
<P>
However, he was quoted as saying Monday that the moves were
necessary because of Panja's resignation.
</P>
<P>
The six-party coalition enjoys a comfortable majority of 237 in
the 385-member Lower House of Parliament. But it must call a
general election before November when its term expires.
</P>
<P>
New cabinet members are expected to be led by the prime
minister to an audience with the king on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
