<HEADLINE> Moya Makes Winning Start in Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Former French Open champion Carlos
Moya of Spain made a winning start at the Estoril Open here on
Tuesday, defeating Romania's Adrian Voinea 6-4, 6-4 to reach the
second round.
</P>
<P>
The Spaniard only returned to play on the ATP Tour in
Scottsdale last month after a stress fracture in his back which
sidelined him for the closing months of last season.
</P>
<P>
Moya next will wait for an opponent from second seed Magnus
Norman of Sweden and Frenchman Jerome Golmard.
</P>
<P>
Austrian Markus Hipfl scored a victory over 1998 champion
Alberto Berasategui of Spain 7-6 (7-3), 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia was playing later, facing
Spaniard Francisco Clavet and trying to escape the first round
here for the only time in five years.
</P>
<P>
In the women's first round, number two Nathalie Dechy of France
defeated Spanish qualifier Nurla Llagostera 7-5, 5-7, 6-3, while
third-seeded Anne-Gaelle Sidot, also a Frenchwoman, overcame
Hungarian Anna Maria Foldenyi 5-7, 6-2, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Spanish sixth seed Cristina Torrens Valero beat Romanian
Catalina Cristea 6-1, 6-2. 
</P>
