<HEADLINE> Haessler to Miss Euro 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, April 11 (Xinhua) -- German national coach Erich
Ribbeck has decided not to include veteran midfielder Thomas
Haessler in his Euro 2000 squad, the TSV 1860 Munich player said
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"He told me I could go ahead and book my summer holidays,"
Haessler said.
</P>
<P>
The 33-year-old earned the last of his 97 caps at the 1998
World Cup. He had hoped a string of impressive performances with
his club would win him a place in the squad for Euro 2000 in
Belgium and the Netherlands from June 10 to July 2.
</P>
<P>
The diminutive midfielder was voted the Player of the
Tournament in the 1992 European Championship in Sweden. 
