<HEADLINE> Taiwan Investment in Xiamen One-Tenth of Total in Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Taiwan's accumulated investment
in Xiamen, a coastal city in eastern China, has taken up
approximately one-tenth of its total investment in the mainland,
Xiamen's vice-mayor Su Shuli said here today.
</P>
<P>
Su told a press conference of the ongoing Fourth China Fair for
International Investment and Trade today that Xiamen, in Fujian
Province, has to date seen over 1,700 Taiwan-invested enterprises
established in the city, with contractual Taiwan investment of 3.5
billion U.S. dollars and paid-in Taiwan capital of three billion U.
S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Su said that a special Taiwan information booth has been set up
at the fair to promote trade and investment across the Taiwan
Straits.  
