<HEADLINE> Diplomatic Envoys from EU Members Visit Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Diplomatic envoys from 14
European Union member countries recently visited east China's
Shandong Province, where they expressed their interest to help
deepen cooperation between EU and this fast growing coastal
province in eastern China.
</P>
<P>
Shandong provincial governor Li Chunting met with the envoys
during their stay, and explained the province's economic and
social development plans. He said Shandong's cooperation with the
EU in economic, scientific, technological and other sectors has
been increasing since the country's reform and opening up.
</P>
<P>
He noted that there's still broad cooperative potential between
them in fields such as intensive agricultural processing, industry,
education, and commerce.
</P>
<P>
The EU is now Shandong's fourth-largest trading partner. All
the 15 EU members have invested in the province, for nearly 900
projects, and a total of 1.29 billion U.S. dollars of EU funding
has been used. 
</P>
</TEXT>
