<DOCNO> XIE20000411.0096 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Diplomatic News Highlights (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua)-- Following are highlights of today'
s diplomatic news released by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
 Chinese President Meets Singapore PM
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here today that China
attaches great attention to its relationship with Singapore, and
considers it an important part of friendly cooperation with
Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark while meeting with Singapore Prime
Minister Goh Chok Tong, who arrived here Sunday on an 11-day
official visit, Goh's fifth visit to China.
</P>
<P>
"This year marks the 10th anniversary of the establishment of
diplomatic relations between China and Singapore and the turn of a
new century," Jiang said, adding that Goh's visit to China at this
juncture has special meaning, and will strongly push forward
bilateral relations of friendly cooperation to new heights.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang said China is satisfied with the development of
relations with Singapore, and hopes to work together for new and
better development of these ties.
</P>
<P>
 CPPCC Chairman Meets Singaporean PM
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), today told
visiting Singaporean Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong that China is
willing to learn from Singapore in modernizing the country.
</P>
<P>
Li said that he was delighted to meet with Goh again in the
blossoming spring in the Chinese capital. He expressed his
admiration for the courage and wisdom of the Singaporean
government and people in handling the difficult situation amidst
the Asian financial crisis and the belief that Goh's current visit
will play an important part in promoting and developing China-
Singapore friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China's reform is "at a critical phase in tackling
tough issues." He said that reform and opening-up drive has
produced remarkable achievements over the past 20 years.
</P>
