<HEADLINE> Taiwan Investment in Mainland Keeps Strong Momentum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Taiwan's investment in the
mainland has kept its strong momentum for the first three months
this year, Assistant Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation Ma Xiuhong told a press conference for the Fourth
China Fair for International Investment and Trade today.
</P>
<P>
This shows that Taiwan businessmen are confident in investing
in the mainland and are optimistic about the prospects of trade
and economic cooperation across the Taiwan Straits, she said.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released by Ma, Taiwan's mainland
investment has kept up with the foreign direct investment in China.
</P>
<P>
The number of newly-authorized foreign-funded enterprises for
the first quarter rose by 13 percent over the same period last
year, and the contractual value went up 46 percent.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan's investment in the mainland is good for its economic
restructuring and benefits both sides, she said. 
