<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Agriculture Minister
Ioan Muresan Tuesday presented a 12-year agricultural development
strategy, putting increasing production and competitiveness,
together with an overall rural development as his main and
permanent objectives.
</P>
<P>
His medium-term priorities are to turn the food industry profit-
making, to raise farmers' income and to prepare for the country's
long-expected admission into the Europe Union, the minister added.
</P>
<P>
The food industry had seen its production reduced because of
bad management, delay in privatization and failure to adjust to
the market economy, Muresan said in the strategy document.
</P>
<P>
