NEW DELHI, April 11 (Xinhua) -- India's infotech giant, Infosys
Technologies Ltd., Tuesday announced a total income of 9.215
billion rupees (214 million U.S. dollars) for the 1999-2000 fiscal
year, 88 percent more than the 5.125 billion rupees (119 million
dollars) for the previous fiscal.
</P>
<P>
The company also posted a net profit at 2.86 billion rupees (66.
5 million dollars), up 115 percent over the 1.33 billion rupees (
30.9 million dollars) in the previous fiscal.
</P>
<P>
Its total income for the fourth quarter ending March 31, 2000,
was 2.86 billion rupees (66.51 million dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
