<HEADLINE> Gold, Silver Prices Up in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Prices of gold and silver
continued to rise on the bullion market Tuesday in Mumbai (Bombay)
on good demand in face of thin supply.
</P>
<P>
Standard gold started firm at 4,480 rupees (104.18 U.S. dollars)
per 10 grams and rose further smartly to end at 4,490 rupees (104.
41 dollars), showing a sharp rise of 15 rupees (0.35 dollars) over
the last close of 4,475 rupees (104.06 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Twenty-two-carat gold was nominally quoted higher at 4,155
rupees(96.63 dollars) per 10 grams from Monday's level of 4,140
rupees(96.28 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, ready silver (.999 fineness) closed at 8,070 rupees(
187.67 dollars) per kilogram, showing a good rise of 40 rupees (0.
93 dollars) over the previous close of 8,030 rupees (186.74
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) also rallied by a similar margin to
7,940 rupees (184.65 dollars) per kilogram from 7,900 rupees (183.
72 dollars). 
</P>
