<HEADLINE> Russia to Permanently Deploy Infantry in Chechnya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The 42nd infantry division of the
Russian armed forces will be permanently deployed in the Republic
of Chechnya by May 1, a senior military official said here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Colonel General Vladislav Putilin, chief of the Mobilization
Department of the Russian General Staff, told reporters that the
division, formed by 30 percent of contract servicemen and 70
percent of conscripts, will be established and deployed in
Chechnya by May 1.
</P>
<P>
All the enlists of the division will receive a six-month
training in military training centers, he added.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the Russian Central Election Commission
(CEC) tentatively scheduled the election of a state Duma (lower
house of the parliament) deputy in Chechnya for August 20. As a
single-mandate electoral district of the Russian Federation, the
republic held no parliamentary election last December due to
Russia's anti-terrorist war there.
</P>
<P>
CEC Chairman Alexander Veshnyakov said the elections of a State
Duma deputy were skipped in Chechnya on December 19, 1999 "because
of the lack of organizational and legal possibilities to hold them
during that period." 
</P>
</TEXT>
