<HEADLINE> Seoul to Put More Interpreting-System Taxis on Streets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The number of taxis with an
interpreting system will be increased to 10,000 in Seoul by the
end of this year for the convenience of foreign passengers.
</P>
<P>
The Planning and Budget Ministry said Tuesday that the move is
aimed at preventing taxi drivers from overcharging foreigners and
letting them off before reaching the destination while helping
drivers to communicate with foreign passengers.
</P>
<P>
Seoul now has only 477 such taxis.
</P>
<P>
A plan to require taxi drivers to issue fare receipts if
requested by passengers is also under consideration, said the
ministry. 
