<HEADLINE> Scientists Study Effect of Environmental Changes On People's Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A group of scientists with the
Chinese Academy of Geology studied the effect of environmental
changes over the past 100 years on people's health in large
industrial cities.
</P>
<P>
Lin Jingxing, a researcher with the academy who heads the
research team, said scientists will further study the relationship
between environmental pollution and the incidence of serious
diseases.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that about a quarter of human diseases are
connected with the environment. Acute respiratory diseases caused
by air pollution kill over four million children worldwide every
year. 
