<HEADLINE> Bayer Polymer Technical Center Set Up in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A foundation-laying ceremony was
held in the Pudong New Area of Shanghai today for a polymer
technical center, a 10 million U.S. dollars project invested by
Bayer (China).
</P>
<P>
The Bayer Polymer Technical Center will be the first of its
kind ever built by the German chemical giant, according to
Reinhard Clausius, head of marketing in Bayer's Polyurethanes
Business Group.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the technical center will help Bayer bring
its polymer technology to China to support local manufacturers of
autos, car parts, electronic products, building materials, shoes
and furniture, the Bayer officer said in an address at the
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The center will mainly engaged in offering related technical
training, research and development, as well as technical and
consulting services.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Bayer has 17 branches in China, including 11 joint
ventures and two solely-owned firms, with a total investment of
more than 700 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Bayer has yearly sales of 500 million U.S. dollars in China,
which now is the German company's second largest market in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Bayer is currently considering moving its Greater China
regional headquarters from Hong Kong to Shanghai, according to Dr.
Michael Portoff, spokesman for Bayer's Greater China regional
headquarters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
