<HEADLINE> CPPCC Members Strongly Refute Lu's Statements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Members of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) in Hong Kong Tuesday strongly refuted Annette
Lu's statements advocating "independence of Taiwan".
</P>
<P>
Participants to a forum on the Taiwan issue said Lu's
statements deny the fact that Taiwan is an inseparable part of the
Chinese territory and that the people of Taiwan are an inseparable
part of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Tsui Sze-man, member of the Standing Committee of the CPPCC
National Committee and director of the Hong Kong Mirror newspaper,
said that in a recent interview with a Hong Kong cable TV station,
Lu openly advocated "Taiwan independence", which challenged the
one-China principle and stirred animosity between the people on
both sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Some CPPCC National Committee members said that the extremists
who do not want to see the cross-straits relationship head toward
peaceful reunification have intentionally fabricated various
stories to separate China, and Annette Lu is the most notorious.
</P>
<P>
Chuang Shih-Ping, member of the Standing Committee of the CPPCC
National Committee and honorary chairman of the Hong Kong South
Pacific Commercial Bank, noted that Lu wrongly advocated "Taiwan
independence" and even tried to rationalize Japan's occupation of
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Chuang said the Chinese history and geography clearly show that
Taiwan is a part of China, and that this can never be changed. The
temporary separation of Taiwan from the motherland will inevitably
come to an end, Chuang said.
</P>
<P>
All the participants warned that anyone attempting to carry out
a "Taiwan independence" policy is doomed to fail. Annette Lu
challenged the 1.25 billion Chinese people who stand behind the
one-China principle, and she intends to push Taiwan into the abyss
of war, they said. 
</P>
