<HEADLINE> India's Industry Grows by 11 Pct in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 11 (Xinhua) -- India's industrial production
recorded an impressive growth rate of 11 percent in February 2000
due to robust growth in manufacturing and electricity sectors, the
Central Statistical Organization said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The healthy growth in industrial production during the month
took the overall performance during the year so far (April 1999-
February 2000) to 7.9 percent as against 7.1 percent recorded a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturing sector, accounting for nearly 80 percent of
the total industrial production, rose by 12 percent in February
this year as against 4.9 percent in February 1999.
</P>
<P>
The electricity sector also showed a marked improvement over
the last year, growing by 9.3 percent in February as against 3.7
percent recorded a year ago. 
</P>
