<HEADLINE> Singapore Forges Broadband Alliance With Foreign Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The Infocomm Development
Authority of Singapore Tuesday signed a memorandum of
understanding with three international players to forge a new
strategic broadband alliance on Singapore One as part of its
strategy to develop the city state into a dynamic and vibrant
infocomm hub.
</P>
<P>
Under the MOU, innovatv.com will offer "interactive video
magazines" on Singapore One while On2.com, Inc. will customize and
deliver a massive database of movie and celebrity information and
Online Media Group will create interactive television and audio
services for it.
</P>
<P>
An official from the authority said the move to forge
partnership with international players aims to bring in
international companies to deploy broadband contents and services
on Singapore One, to expand the range and diversity of contents
and applications for its users and to create opportunities for
local and international online players to share and exchange
expertise and experience and use Singapore One as the launch pad
to access the Asian market.
</P>
<P>
Singapore One, developed by both multinational and innovative
local companies, was launched in 1998 and it now provides high-
speed interactive and multimedia applications and services for
users. 
