<DOCNO> XIE20000411.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU, Euro Zone GDP Grows in 4th Quarter of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The gross domestic product (GDP)
grew in both the European Union (EU) and the euro zone in the
fourth quarter of last year, Eurostat reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical bureau of the European
Community said the GDP grew by 0.8 percent in the 15-nation bloc
in the period, while it increased by 0.9 percent in the 11-nation
single currency zone.
</P>
<P>
The Eurostat attributed the economic growth mainly to the
increase in final consumption expenditures of private households
and the rise in exports.
</P>
<P>
Consumption rose by 0.8 percent in the EU and 0.7 percent in
the euro zone.
</P>
<P>
Exports jumped 1.3 percent and 1.5 percent in the EU and the
euro zone  respectively.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same period of 1998, the GDP in the EU and
the euro zone grew both by 3 percent.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, the economy in both the EU and the euro zone grew by 2.
3 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat said although most of the EU member states experienced
slowdown in the fourth quarter of last year, the Netherlands and
Finland recorded acceleration of growth at a pace of 1.2 percent
and 1.3 percent respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
