<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Test Fires New Medium Range Naval Missile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The missile, named "Dhanush" which means bow in Hindi, was
fired from naval ship INS Subhadra anchored some 20 km from the
coast of the eastern state of Orissa at 1:35 p.m. Tuesday and had
a perfect lift-off, the PTI quoted defense sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The 8.56-meter sleek missile, the first of its kind, has been
exclusively developed for the navy and considered as the naval
version of Prithvi, another type of missile India developed
indigenously, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The outcome of the test firing would be fully known after
analyzing the data collected from different tracking and telemetry
centers, they said.
</P>
<P>
According to the PTI, scientists from India's Defense Research
and Development Organization closely monitored the test firing.
</P>
<P>
India has already equipped its army with the 150 km range
Prithvi I surface-to-surface missile, while the 250 km Prithvi II,
being developed for the air force, is also near completion, the
PTI said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
