<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 11 (Xinhua) -- ASEAN Chamber of Commerce
and Industry President Tajudin Ramli has urged ASEAN to prepare a
new framework on how it could meaningfully take part in the
process of globalization.
</P>
<P>
The sector that urgently requires the framework or guidelines
is the services sector which covers financial services,
telecommunications, multimedia and air services, he said at a
press conference after the second ASEAN Business Summit 2000 was
officially opened here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He said a new framework is needed because the ASEAN business
community is not convinced that the existing framework on
globalization can protect their interest.
</P>
<P>
The preparation of the framework is part of capacity building
to meet with the challenges of globalization, Tajudin Ramli said,
adding the other ways to build on ASEAN's capacity to face the
challenges include the physical infrastructure and human resources.
</P>
<P>
The two-day business summit was officiated by Deputy Prime
Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi representing Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad who is in Havana to attend the G-77 summit.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups Brunei, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia,
Myanmar,the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam. 
</P>
