<HEADLINE> China Provides Humanitarian Aid to DPRK Nationals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua)-- China has provided humanitarian
aid to nationals of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (
DPRK) who illegally crossed the border into Chinese territory in
recent years, said Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi.
</P>
<P>
Sun made the remark at a regular press conference here today,
in response to a question about this situation.
</P>
<P>
He said the since the DPRK met with some temporary economic
difficulties, a small number of DPRK citizens illegally crossed
the border into China because of economic hardships in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
China, as a close neighbor of the DPRK, has provided
humanitarian support to those DPRK nationals in line with the
traditional friendship between the two countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
But according to international law and their purpose for
crossing the border into China, Sun said, they are not refugees.
</P>
<P>
China has always treated them in a friendly manner and from a
humanitarian perspective, and repatriated them in accordance with
common international practice, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that China has always dealt with this issue from the
perspective of maintaining peace and stability on the Korean
Peninsula. 
</P>
</TEXT>
