<HEADLINE> China Independently Develops Satellite Perigee Solid Kick Motor: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman Sun Yuxi today reaffirmed that China has developed the
satellite perigee kick motor, known as EPKM, entirely relying on
its own efforts.
</P>
<P>
At a regular press conference in response to a relevant
question, he said that China has noticed media reports saying that
Lockheed Martin of the United States was involved in the
development of the motor.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that a spokesman of China Great Wall Industry
Corporation had made the issue clear the other day.
</P>
<P>
The so-called allegation that China had probably acquired
technical assistance from Lockheed Martin in the development of
the EPKM is groundless, said Sun.
</P>
<P>
"We have also noticed that Lockheed Martin has denied these
charges", Sun noted.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Asia Satellite Telecommunications Co. Ltd. is
not the holding company of the China International Trust and
Investment Corp. (CITIC), and CITIC, as a shareholder of the Asia
Satellite Telecommunications Co. Ltd., has not been engaged
directly in the business activities of the satellite
Telecommunications company.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that the normal exchanges between China and the U.S.
in economic, trade, scientific and technological fields conform to
the common interests of the people of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
What the U.S. government should do is to safeguard the normal
exchanges between the two countries in the economic, trade, and
scientific and technological fields, instead of setting up
obstacles to intervene the normal development of bilateral
exchanges, he said.
</P>
<P>
Any attempt to stick to a Cold War mentality and destroy Sino-U.
S. relations is doomed to failure, Sun said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
