<HEADLINE> PLA Speeds up Training For Armament Command Officers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The People's Liberation Army (PLA)
is speeding up the training of its middle-ranking armament command
officers, in a move to improve their policy-making, coordination
and research capacities.
</P>
<P>
An official with the General Armament Department of the PLA
said the move is taken to meet the requirement of the PLA's
purchase, management and maintenance of armaments.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that the PLA launch large-scale training
of armament command officers.
</P>
<P>
According to a regulation adopted earlier this month by the PLA
's General Armament Department, all armament command personnel
will be trained at the Institute of Armament Command attached to
the General Armament Department before they become middle-ranking
officers.
</P>
<P>
The official said the training include two specialties --
armament purchase and management and maintenance of military
equipment. These specialties will deal with military operations,
joint campaigns and maintenance of military equipment during
battles.
</P>
<P>
The Institute of Armament Command has spent over 3 million
yuan (361,000 U.S. dollars) in building eight multi-media
classrooms, rebuilding exercise centers and several special
classrooms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
