<HEADLINE> Library to Serve Readers with One Card </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Patrons of the National Library
of China now will be able to read, borrow books, or eat there by
using just one card.
</P>
<P>
Launched by the library and the Beijing Branch of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China, the Peony Library Readers
Card will take the place of all present cards for reading and
borrowing books.
</P>
<P>
Along with library services, the card can also be used as an
ordinary cash card to deposit and withdraw cash and shop in
department stores.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Heping, vice president of the library, said that readers
will benefit from the card by saving time and trouble, and this
demonstrates that the library has greatly enhanced its efficiency
and office automation.
</P>
<P>
Readers can apply for the card beginning tomorrow, and more
readers than ever, including both Chinese and foreigners above the
age of 18, will be able to avail themselves of the library's
services.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a temporary card will be issued for use in the
library only. 
</P>
</TEXT>
