<HEADLINE> Japan Gives Volcano Monitoring Equipment to Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Japan turned over here Tuesday a
set of seismic and volcanic activities monitoring equipment to the
Philippines, Philippine News Agency(PNA) said.
</P>
<P>
The set of equipment, amounting to 850 million Japanese yen (2.
18 million U.S. dollars) was officially presented by Tsukasa
Kawada,representative of the Japanese government, to the
Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology (Phivolcs).
</P>
<P>
According to the PNA, the equipment was designed to upgrade the
monitoring and early warning capabilities of the Phivolcs by
replacing all obsolete equipment at the Institute's headquarters
and at its 34 existing monitoring stations.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the improvement to the local earthquake and
volcano monitoring system will reduce or mitigate the loss of life
and damage to property caused by seismic and volcanic activities
in the Philippines. 
