<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Export Growth Likely to Slow Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's exports this year
are expected to enjoy continued growth but at a slower pace,
International Trade and Industry Minister Rafidah Aziz said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This was due to the economic slow down of the country's biggest
market, the United States, which maintained a share of 21.9
percent of Malaysia's exports with 70.4 billion ringgit (18.526
billion U.S. dollars) in 1999, the minister said at her ministry's
annual trade and industry dialogue with Electrical and electronic
(E&AMP;E) associations and wood-based industry associations here.
</P>
<P>
"The growth in exports was mainly due to strong demand from
industrialized countries and economic recovery in the Asian region,
" she was quoted by Bernama News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
In the first two months of 2000, exports reached 52.5 billion
ringgit (13.815 billion dollars) with E&AMP;E products remaining the
largest export earner with 29.8 billion ringgit (7.842 billion
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Rafidah said that to develop and enhance export capabilities of
local companies, the government has launched two programs, namely,
industrial linkage program and global supplier program aimed at
fostering linkages and integration between SMI and large
corporations both locally and overseas as their suppliers.
</P>
<P>
She said in developing and strengthening the export markets,
the government has planned some 203 trade promotion programs in
the established and less established markets throughout this year.
</P>
<P>
The government is also assisting local companies to identify
and explore new markets through the Malaysian External Trade
Development Corporation (Matrade) which provides various market
information and online communications facilities through its
homepage, she said.
</P>
<P>
The minister urged companies to create their own websites to
promote their products and link up with Matrade in export
promotion and establish business networks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
