<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Seizes More Heroin Haul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka police has seized 1.72
kg of smuggled heroin following the arrest of a woman at the
Colombo International Airport, Police said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan woman is said to be a nurse by profession who is
domiciled in Pakistan. The heroin was detected under several under-
wears worn by the woman, Police Narcotics Bureau (PNB) officials
said.
</P>
<P>
She had arrived in Sri Lanka Monday by SU 543 flight from
Pakistan.She had travelled to Sri Lanka almost every two months.
</P>
<P>
The PNB seized 38.4 kilograms of smuggled heroin in March this
year at the airport, the largest ever haul in the country recent
years.
</P>
<P>
Interpol has identified Sri Lanka as a major transit point in
international drug smuggling due to its strategic location between
two main drug producing areas -- the Golden Triangle of Myanmar,
Thailand and Laos and the Golden Crescent comprising Pakistan,
Afghanistan and Iran.
</P>
<P>
Most of the drugs that enter Sri Lanka were smuggled out
through commercial flights or container cargo from the port,
police said.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's law enforcement officers caught 68.5 kilograms of
heroin in 1999, a 40 percent rise over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
However, detection of drugs had risen sharply in 2000. In the
first three months the PNB had recovered 55 kg of heroin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
