<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhang Holds on to Win Ericsson CPGA Challenge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANSHA, Guangdong Province, April 11 (Xinhua) -- China's top
golfer Zhang Lianwei rolled to win the Ericsson China PGA
Challenge with a 5-under-par 129 at the Nansha Golf Club on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Coming into the second day with 4-under 68, Zhang maintained
his form to extend a 2-stroke lead to four more to win his first
competition this year.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Wengen took the second place with 1-under while Qi Zengfa,
from the city of Shenzhen with Zhang, was at third with four
further back at 137.
</P>
<P>
But Zhang needed some luck to hold his lead at the hole 14.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Jun, winner of the 1997 World China Tour in Beijing,
closed up the gap to one stroke trailing to Zhang at hole 10, but
hit a double bogey at 14 to fall back again.
</P>
<P>
"I really felt great pressure at 10 when I hit a bad putt,"
said Zhang, who won the second place in the 1998 Bangkok Asian
Games. "But Cheng also made mistake at 14 to give me a breath."
</P>
<P>
Cheng, who is in the same Shenzhen Golf Club as Zhang, said, "I
didn't think much then, but just wanted to save my par. But maybe
I should be more careful to have a par or even a bogey."
</P>
<P>
Lin Shaoru won the women's game with 1-under-par 133 when she
struck a 2-under 70 on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Yang Hongmei was second with four more strokes, followed by
Zhang Lichun with two more back. 
</P>
</TEXT>
