<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Must Join WTO: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 11 (Xinhua) -- An Iranian official on Tuesday
underlined the urgency of Iran's entry into the World Trade
Organization (WTO), calling it an "inevitable necessity."
</P>
<P>
Sooner or later Iran should join the WTO, and any delay in
joining the world organization will create problems for the
country's production units, said Hussein Naji, deputy industries
minister for non-ferrous industries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to a gathering of industrialists in Gachsaran, capital
of the western Kohkiluyeh-Boyer Ahmad Province, the official also
called for greater banking facilities for industrial units, the
Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
He pointed to the liberalization of the country's industry
sector as one of the main features of the third five-year plan
(2000-2005).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the governor-general of the province, Karim
Shurangiz, stressed the importance of the acquisition of expertise
and modern technical know-how in the industrial sector.
</P>
<P>
He said directors and industrialists equipped with the latest
academic and technical knowledge are prerequisites to the progress
of an industry, IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, several Iranian officials urged the government
to consider the WTO membership, but many experts noted that Iran's
industries will face a serious challenge if the country joins the
world trade body. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
