<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Airways to Increase Flights for Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Airways International
Plc. (THAI), Thailand's national flag carrier, will increase
flights and seats on domestic routes to serve the general public
during the Songkran Festival his week, the official Thai News
Agency said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
THAI President Thamnoon Wanglee said that the airlines would
provide seven extra flights on the return Bangkok-Phuket route
during the Songkran or Water Throwing Festival between April 13
and 16 to serve local and foreign tourists wanting to join the
traditional Thai New Year event in the country.
</P>
<P>
Boeing B747-400 and Airbus A300-600 aircraft, which can
accommodate 389-405 and 260 passengers, respectively, would be
used to serve the Songkran travelers, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Bangkok International Airport has also reportedly been
prepared to serve increasing passengers and tourists during the
traditional event, which officially falls between April 13 and 15.
</P>
<P>
Several provinces in the country have started the Songkran
Festival since late last week.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of thousands of Thais and foreign tourists are
expected to join the Songkran Festival in all regions of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
