<HEADLINE> Leeds United Profit Soars  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 11 (Xinhua) -- With success in European and
domestic games, English premier league soccer club Leeds United
gained a 89 percent increase in operating profit for the club's
parent company.
</P>
<P>
Parent company Leeds Sporting Plc posted an operating profit
before clearing player debts of 6.4 million pounds (10 million U.S.
dollars) in the six months to the end of December, up from 3.4
million in the previous year, on turnover of 29.3 million.
</P>
<P>
Television revenue jumped 49 percent to 7.0 million pounds
while ticket sales rose 49 percent to 6.1 million and merchanding
rose 42 percent to 2.7 million.
</P>
<P>
"Together with further squad development, lucrative new
sponsorship agreements and the prospect of perhaps participating
in (next season's) Champions League, we have strong grounds to be
optimistic about the future," Leeds Sporting said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Leeds are third in the premier league and are also in the UEFA
Cup semi-final, which has been overshadowed by two of their fans
being stabbed to death in Istanbul before the first leg against
Galatasaray last week. 
</P>
