<HEADLINE> China's Major Air-conditioner Maker Slashes Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Chunlan Group, a major air-
conditioner manufacturer in China, has slashed its prices
drastically, with reduction in some models exceeding 1,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
However, six other major air-conditioner manufacturers
including Gree, Haier, and Changhong announced that they would not
involve themselves in the price war, "China Business Daily"
reported.
</P>
<P>
Chunlan, whose annual air-conditioner output tops two million,
said it did not wish to wage price wars against other
manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
China's air-conditioner industry has been growing steadily over
the past years. However, the fast-growing industry has outstripped
demand, glutting the market with oversupply.
</P>
<P>
Some ten million air-conditioners were sold last year in China,
one million surplus goods were left in warehouses.
</P>
<P>
The profit margin of air-conditioners is estimated by some
analysts at ten percent.
</P>
<P>
The availability of air-conditioners in China stands at 20
percent in urban areas, much lower than the 90 percent coverage of
color TV sets. Sales of air-conditioners accounted for only half
of color TV sets last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
