<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand, U.S., Singapore to Hold Joint Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The armed forces of Thailand,
Singapore and the United States will conduct the 19th Exercise
Cobra Gold in Thailand from May 9 to 23, representatives of the
three countries announced here Tuesday at a joint press conference.
</P>
<P>
Cobra Gold 2000 is a regularly scheduled joint exercise and is
the latest in the continuing series of U.S.-Thai military
exercises designed to ensure regional peace and strengthen the
ability of the Royal Thai armed forces to defend Thailand or
regional contingencies, an army spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
This year, for the first time, at the invitation of Thai armed
forces 29 Singaporean soldiers will participate in the exercise,
which is one of the largest exercises involving U.S. forces in the
Pacific Command this year.
</P>
<P>
"We think it is a good opportunity for us to learn from Thai
and U.S. armed forces," Colonel Jerry Soh, defense attache of the
Singaporean embassy to Thailand told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The 29 Singaporean military staff will be assigned to different
parts of the exercise, allowing them to have a comprehensive
understanding of the exercise, Soh said.
</P>
<P>
But he refused to say whether the Singaporean forces will be
more involved in this exercise in the future.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia and the Philippines were invited to be observers of
the exercise.
</P>
<P>
The exercise will focus on peace enforcement operations,
including planning and execution of a noncombatant evacuation
operation.
</P>
<P>
This type of military operations is increasingly called for in
today's world and are more likely than a major theater war, said a
press release of the U.S. embassy here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Colonel Lance Booth, chief of Joint U.S. Military Advisory
Group Thailand (JUSMAGTHAI), told Xinhua that the goal of the
exercise is to help Thailand to be prepared in case of crisis. He
attributed the good performance of Thai armed forces in
peacekeeping mission last year in East Timor to the exercise.
</P>
<P>
He denied that the U.S. wants to involve all ASEAN countries in
exercise.
</P>
<P>
As in all previous Cobra Gold exercises, this year's exercise
will include joint-combined land and air operations, combined
naval operations, amphibious operations and special operations.
</P>
<P>
A total of 13,196 U.S. forces will participate, including
elements of U.S. army, Pacific; U.S. Marine Corps Forces, Pacific;
as well as Special Operations Command Pacific , Air Combat Command,
Air Mobility Command, and reserve elements from the army, navy,
air force and marine corps.
</P>
<P>
Participating Thai forces will amount to 7,100, from army, navy,
marine corps and air force.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 112 aircraft and 13 naval vessels will be deployed.
Among the aircraft to be used are C-130 cargo plane, F-18 fighting
jet, AV-8 marine airplane, EA-6 anti-missile airplane and various
kinds of helicopters, Major Dave Teel, JUSMAGTHAI air operations
officer told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
U.S. aircraft carrier Kitty Hawk will also be deployed in the
exercise, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
