<HEADLINE> Kenya to Reduce Defence Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan Chief of General Staff
Daudi Tonje has said that the country's defence force will be
reduced to a small well- equipped and well-trained troop.
</P>
<P>
The Daily Nation newspaper on Tuesday quoted Tonje as saying
such a force can effectively defend the country from any external
aggression.
</P>
<P>
Tonje told reporters at the weekend during the annual march and
shoot exercise in Oldonyo Marushi area of Kajiado District in
southern Kenya that "there is no need for us to have a large armed
force which is not well- equipped and not well-trained."
</P>
<P>
"The dimension of attack from the enemy has now changed. We
need a small well-equipped and well-trained personnel for swift
action and movement," Tonje said.
</P>
<P>
However, the general did not disclose Kenya's defence strength
or the number to be reduced.
</P>
<P>
So far, Kenya's defence is divided in three arms, namely the
Kenya army, the air force and the navy. 
</P>
