<HEADLINE> Fujian Builds Museum for Historical Sites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Fujian Province, east China, is
building its first Cultural Relics Museum, and its first-phase
construction has been completed.
</P>
<P>
The Museum is located at the Tanshi Mountain historical site,
which is dating some 4,000 to 5,000 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Numerous cultural relics and tombs have been unearthed at the
site, since it was first discovered in 1954.
</P>
<P>
The Museum, with a floor space of 8,120 square meters, covers a
total area of 28,000 square meters, It includes a center for
scientific research, a site of archaeological excavation, and a
collection of sculptures, said Ou Tansheng, curator of the Museum.
