<DOCNO> XIE20000411.0266 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Up Waste Disposal System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 11 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Science and
Technology will introduce a waste disposal system in Guanghan, a
city in southwest China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
With a population of 400,000, Guanghan, 30 kilometers north of
the provincial capital of Chengdu, produced about 400 tons of
urban waste a day.
</P>
<P>
The Sanfeng Science and Technology Industrial Company has three
urban waste disposal system with a combined handling capacity of
700 tons of waste per day.
</P>
<P>
The 400-ton production line can produce 100,000 tons to 200,000
tons of compound fertilizers annually, generating 2.4 million yuan
in profit per year, said Wang Yingbin, general manager of the
Company.
</P>
<P>
He said "Rubbish in cities is absolutely not waste. It is the
only resource that can maintain sustainable growth on Earth."
</P>
<P>
Wang started the Company in cooperation with the local
government and the Ministry of Science and Technology with a total
investment of 6.2 million yuan in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the common practice of burying waste, the new
waste disposal system not only saves land, but also helps prevent
environment pollution, saving the local government 400,000 yuan
each year, according to Wang.
</P>
<P>
Random disposal of garbage takes up large areas of land and
seriously pollutes air, rivers, lakes and ground water.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government allocated 2.18 billion yuan (265 million
U.S. dollars ) last year to waste disposal techniques.
</P>
<P>
The per capita garbage production in some 666 cities is 440
kilograms each year, with the annual volume growing by 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Garbage dumps on 500 million square meters of land surround
than 200 Chinese cities, according to an earlier report by "
Science Times".
</P>
<P>
However, the environment and air quality in Guanghan has
greatly improved due to the new waste disposal systems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
