<HEADLINE> China's Inland City Renews Website for Surfers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Shijiazhuang, capital city of
Hebei Province, recently renewed the homepage of its website on
the Internet to facilitate web surfers.
</P>
<P>
As one of first batch of provincial capital websites in China,
Shijiazhuang's homepage http://www.shijiazhuang.gov.cn has
attracted more than 100,000 visitors with more substantial content
and new pictures, according to Beijing Review in English version.
</P>
<P>
The website has 38 columns in eight sections in Chinese,
describing the general situation of Shijiazhuang, foreign fund
invitations, history and culture, tourism, and the daily news.
Its six sections in English cover fields such as politics, economy,
history, education and culture.
</P>
<P>
Information on more than 30 famous enterprises in Shijiazhuang
and over 80 programs aiming to invite foreign funds are also
available on the website.
</P>
<P>
The website has become an important window into Shijiazhuang.
Some foreign citizens who are interested in Shijiazhuang have also
been able to raise questions about the ancient city through the
webpage.
</P>
<P>
The Shijiazhuang municipal government launched the website in
September 1998 and after one year construction, the website has
made much progress in information capacity and service function.
</P>
