<HEADLINE> China's Papermaking Industry Needs More Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- China's papermaking industry
needs 490 billion yuan (60 billion U.S. dollars) more in
investment to sustain its supply in the face of growing demand,
today's "Economic Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
By 2015, China's total consumption of paper and cardboard will
have amounted to 80 million tons, according to the China
Papermaking Association.
</P>
<P>
The demand requires an increase of production capacity which
calls for an extra 490 billion yuan investment, or an annual 32
billion yuan (3.9 billion U.S. dollars) investment.
</P>
<P>
The papermaking association estimates the increased production
capacity of paper and cardboard in 2015 will be 43 million tons,
while pulp will be 4.3 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Experts call for new ways of money-raising on the part of paper
manufacturers to tackle the money shortage.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
