<HEADLINE> Internet Important to The Economy: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A latest survey by the China
Business Climate Monitoring Center shows 85 percent respondents
consider the Internet important to the national economy.
</P>
<P>
The survey published in today's "China Securities" was carried
out among more than 500 educated Chinese in three major cities of
Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou. More than half of the respondents
use the Internet.
</P>
<P>
More than 90 percent believe that the development of Internet
will lead to fundamental changes in the economy. 
</P>
