<HEADLINE> Sino-Egyptian Presidential Summit Important: Ambassador (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The forthcoming summit between
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
to be held in Alexandria, Egypt, is not only a meeting between
leaders of two friendly countries, but also between close friends,
according to the Egyptian ambassador to China, Mohamed Noman Galal.
</P>
<P>
The presidential summit will push Sino-Egyptian relations of
strategic cooperation forward, the ambassador said in a recent
interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Noting the significance of the summit, the ambassador said that
the two presidents have a deep friendship, and the two countries
enjoy solid relations of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Egypt is the first developing country to establish relations of
strategic cooperation with China, and also the first Arab and
African nation to forge diplomatic relations with the People's
Republic of China, he added.
</P>
