<HEADLINE> Sino-Egyptian Presidential Summit Important: Ambassador (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Both countries are old civilizations, and bilateral relations
have developed continuously thanks to the efforts made by several
generations of respective leaderships, Galal said.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin visited Egypt in 1996, the ambassador
said. President Mubarak has visited China seven times. During his
last China visit in April last year, the two sides reached a
consensus on establishing relations of strategic cooperation
geared toward the 21st century, Galal said.
</P>
<P>
These visits have played an important role in consolidating
Sino-Egyptian friendship and further promoting the development of
bilateral relations, said the ambassador.
</P>
<P>
Egypt plays a unique role in regional and international arenas,
and has an even more important role to play in the Middle East
peace process, the ambassador said, adding that China, as a
permanent member of the United Nations Security Council, plays an
importance role in the international political arena.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said he believes that the summit will be
conducive to moving forward the peace process. 
