<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Singapore PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here today that China attaches great attention to its
relationship with Singapore, and considers it an important part of
friendly cooperation with Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark while meeting with Singapore Prime
Minister Goh Chok Tong, who arrived here Sunday on an 11-day
official visit, Goh's fifth visit to China.
</P>
<P>
"This year marks the 10th anniversary of the establishment of
diplomatic relations between China and Singapore and the turn of a
new century," Jiang said, adding that Goh's visit to China at this
juncture has special meaning, and will strongly push forward
bilateral relations of friendly cooperation to new heights.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang said China is satisfied with the development of
relations with Singapore, and hopes to work together for new and
better development of these ties.
</P>
<P>
Goh told Jiang he had had "very good" discussions with other
Chinese leaders, and that they reached consensus on further
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and Goh also exchanged views on the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Goh said that Singapore considers Taiwan a province of China,
and the issue of Taiwan an internal issue of China. He pledged
that the government of Singapore will continue to uphold its one-
China policy.
</P>
<P>
Jiang explained to Goh China's stance on the Taiwan issue,
saying that the principled policy in resolving the Taiwan issue --
"peaceful reunification and one country, two systems" -- has
remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
"Under the one-China principle, we can discuss whatever topics
(with the Taiwan side)," Jiang said. "But we will never promise
not to use force, and we will never allow Taiwan independence in
any form."
</P>
<P>
Vice Chairman of the Central Committee of the Taiwan Democratic
Self-Government League Li Minkuan and Singapore Minister for Law
and Foreign Minister Shunmugam Jayakumar also attended the meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
