<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice President Meets Singapore PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice President Hu Jintao
told visiting Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong here today
that China hopes the two countries will explore new ways and
methods for enhancing bilateral cooperation to push the Sino-
Singaporean friendship and relations of cooperation to a new phase.
</P>
<P>
Hu welcomed Goh and his party to visit China on the special
occasion of the tenth anniversary of the establishment of
diplomatic relations between China and Singapore. Thanks to
concerted efforts, Hu said, these relations have experienced
smooth growth during the past ten years.
</P>
<P>
"Frequent high-level contacts between our two countries play an
important role in the healthy and steady growth of bilateral
relations," he said, adding that further expansion and promotion
of bilateral relations "are well-grounded and have broad prospects.
"
</P>
<P>
In reply, Goh said that Singapore values its ties with China,
and that the current visit, aimed at further advancing Singapore-
China relations, is the fifth he has made since becoming premier.
</P>
<P>
Singapore also has paid great attention to China's strategy of
developing its western region, he said, noting that he will visit
Xi'an, capital of northwest China's Shaanxi Province, this
afternoon. The Singaporean government encourages more
entrepreneurs to invest in China, he said.
</P>
<P>
Goh said that he hopes the top leaders of the two countries
will continue their frequent meetings to secure new growth in
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Hu also briefed the guests on the Chinese
government's principled stand on the Taiwan issue and on China's
strategy for developing the western region and the situation in
that part of China.  
</P>
