<HEADLINE> Sino-French Scientists Apply Remote Sensing Tech to Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and French scientists are
applying remote sensing technology to increase agricultural output
and promote environment-friendly agriculture.
</P>
<P>
A bilateral symposium was held recently in Beijing to promote
the cooperation, which started in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Tong Qingxi, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences,
said during the symposium that remote sensing technology may
monitor the outbreaks of crop diseases and insect rampage.
</P>
<P>
The information of remote sensing is significant to the policy-
makers of the country, the dealers on futures markets, and the
farmers, noted Tong.
</P>
<P>
The remote sensing result will also direct farmers on watering
and fertilizing to economize resources and decrease environmental
pollution. 
</P>
