<HEADLINE> HK to Chair PECC Meeting in Dalian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 11 (Xinhua) -- William Fung, chairman of the
Hong Kong Committee for Pacific Economic Cooperation (HKCPEC),
will lead the Hong Kong delegation to attend the Standing
Committee meeting of the Pacific Economic Cooperation Council (
PECC) scheduled for April 13 and 14 in the northeast China city of
Dalian.
</P>
<P>
Fung will chair the Standing Committee meeting (SC), the first
since Hong Kong assumed the PECC chairmanship in October 1999.
</P>
<P>
The SC meeting provides a good opportunity for "setting a clear
direction for the PECC's work in 2000 and beyond," a HKCPEC
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The SC meeting will discuss, among other issues, the PECC's
trade policy agenda, initiatives for strengthening the financial
markets and corporate governance, and capacity building
initiatives for developing economies.
</P>
<P>
To further cultivate the PECC's relationship with other
international economic and trade organizations, representatives
from Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation and the Pacific Basin
Economic Council have been invited to attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The PECC is a non-governmental organization set up in 1980 with
the purpose of developing closer cooperation among economies in
the region on trade and economic policy issues. Currently, it has
24 member committees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
