<HEADLINE> Malaysia May Buy Russian Helicopters: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia may buy the Russian-
made MI-17 multi-role helicopters to replace the aging Nuri
helicopters, Defense Minister Najib Tun Razak said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Royal Malaysian Air Force (RMAF) may consider buying a
fleet of 10 MIs initially, Najib told reporters after opening the
7th Defence Services Asia Exhibition and Conference here.
</P>
<P>
However, he did not specify which version or the costs involved,
saying "we've not yet gone into actual contract. Still negotiating.
"
</P>
<P>
The minister said there are still few matters to be ironed out
such as the technical specifications.
</P>
<P>
The MI-17 is manufactured by Kazan Helicopters, one of the
primary manufacturers of medium-sized helicopters in the world.
</P>
<P>
Currently two MI-17s are in service with the Fire and Rescue
Service in Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The RMAF has acquired 16 Russian-made MiG-29 fighter jets and
two MiG-29UB combat trainers under a 1994 contract. 
</P>
