<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed lower here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 19 points lower at 2,139 with a turnover
of 251 million NZ dollars (125 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, AMP gained 50 cents to 1,911 cents,
and Air New Zealand-B 20 to 275 cents due to the fact that
Singapore Airlines has bought a 8.3 percent stake in the airline.
</P>
<P>
All Fletcher Challenge stocks maintained downward with Energy
falling 20 cents to 490 cents, Building 5 to 220 cents, Forests 2
to 74 cents, and Paper one cent to 228 cents.
</P>
<P>
