<HEADLINE> Singapore Air Takes Air New Zealand Stake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Airlines (SIA) moved
quickly Tuesday to gain a chunk of Air New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
Television New Zealand reported the Singaporean airlines spent
70 million U.S.dollars to buy an 8.3 percent stake in New Zealand'
s carrier.
</P>
<P>
It followed Monday night's New Zealand government approval of
SIA taking a stake of up to 8.3 percent in Air New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
SIA's raid was on Air New Zealand-B shares, the only ones
foreign airlines can hold. No foreign airline is allowed to own
more than 25 percent of Air New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
SIA is expected to also do a deal with Brierley Investment for
more shares of Air New Zealand. Brierley Investments owns 47
percent of Air New Zealand. It holds 16.7 percent of Air New
Zealand-B shares. 
</P>
