<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Plans to Set up Export Processing Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government is
considering the establishment of Export Processing Zones (EPZ) in
strategic locations of the country to promote investment in the
manufacturing industry.
</P>
<P>
According to Tuesday's Times of Zambia newspaper, the
government was seriously looking at this issue, saying that it is
expected to set up zones in the agro processing industry which
was the key sector to the economic and sustainable development of
this country.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that the ministries of finance and commerce were
still doing some consultations on this matter to review the
consensus and their progressive program.
</P>
<P>
The pre-study was undertaken by the Ministry of Commerce in
1998 and it was discovered that the free zones in the context of
Zambia being landlocked could not be operated in the same manner
with countries that had direct access to the sea ports.
</P>
<P>
The study proposed a modification of traditional processing
zone format to suit the Zambian situation.
</P>
<P>
Zambia was still learning from the experience of Egypt and
Kenya on how they have established the processing zones, the paper
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
