<HEADLINE> Education Website Opened in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A website devoted to the
continuous education of the Chinese people officially opened here
today.
</P>
<P>
The website: www.eol.com.cn, created by the Enterprises Group
of prestigious Qinghua University, is targeting visitors between
the ages of 16 and 35 who are open-minded and keen on learning.
</P>
<P>
This age group also account for about 75 percent of the country
's Internet accessors, observers say.
</P>
<P>
Along with education information, the website also provides
services such as overseas studies, job seeking, and MBA education.
</P>
