<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Defence Services Asia Exhibition Opens in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The Defence Services Asia
2000 (DSA 2000) exhibition opened here Tuesday, with the presence
of Malaysian Defence Minister Najib Tun Razak.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, the 7th in its series, is the world's first
major defence exhibition in the new century and is the world's
second largest specialized event exclusively for the tri-services,
paramilitary and security services, after Dubai's Idex.
</P>
<P>
Some 420 companies from 39 countries are taking part in the
four-day exhibition. Among the participating countries are
Australia,Britain, Brazil, Bosnia, Cambodia, China, France,
Germany, Italy,Iran, South Africa, Spain and the United States.
</P>
<P>
In conjunction with the event, a high-level conference with the
theme "War, Peace, Globalisation and Asian Security" will be held
Wednesday and Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Several joint-ventures and memoranda of understanding (MoUs)
are expected to be signed between international manufacturers and
local entrepreneurs during the event.
</P>
<P>
The event would enhance Malaysia's position as one of the most
attractive investment hubs in the region and even in the world and
will be the catalyst in boosting the development and expansion of
the domestic defence industry, now more so with the growing
confidence in the country's economic recovery, Najib said in a
message to the DSA 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
