<DOCNO> XIE20000411.0320 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sugar Output Falls in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cane crushing season completed toward end-March when the
country's sugar mills switched off their boilers.
</P>
<P>
A latest report of the PSMA said with an average recovery rate
of 8.32 percent sucrose from the sugarcane, sugar factories have
produced 2.412 million tons of sugar. This year the cane quantity
crushed dropped by one million tons to 29 million tons against the
figures recorded last year.
</P>
<P>
At the start of the season in October-November 1999, the
government had predicted that the production figures would reach
the 3.5 million tons mark.
</P>
<P>
Domestic requirement of the commodity is calculated at about
three million tons. Thus there is a gap of about 0.6 million tons
in the production and consumption figures.
</P>
<P>
To fill the gap, importers have already started booking of
cargoes in the international market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
