<HEADLINE> Russian Pair Take Olympic Qualifying Duet Title  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Olga Brousnikina and Maria
Kisseleva from Russia won the duet title at the Synchronised
Swimming Olympic qualifying event in Sydney on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian pair collected four perfect scores of 10 in their
free routine.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Miya Tachibana and Miho Takeda finished second, and
France's Virginie Dedieu and Myriam Lignot came third.
</P>
<P>
The top 20 in Tuesday's competition qualified directly for the
Sydney Olympic Games. The other competitors have a swim-off on
Thursday for four remaining Olympic places. 
</P>
