<HEADLINE> China, Singapore Issue Joint Statement on Bilateral Cooperation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua)-- The Chinese Government and
Singaporean Government issued a joint statement on bilateral
cooperation here today. The full text of the statement goes as
follows:
</P>
<P>
Joint Statement on Bilateral Cooperation Between the
Government of the People's Republic of China and the Government of
the Republic of Singapore
</P>
<P>
1. China and Singapore established diplomatic relations on
October 3, 1990 based on the principles enshrined in the Charter
of the United Nations and the Five Principles of Peaceful
Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
In the past ten years, China and Singapore have enjoyed a close
and long-standing friendship built upon mutual trust and goodwill.
The excellent bilateral relations are underpinned by multi-level
and broad-based cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Singapore recognizes that there is only one China and that
Taiwan is part of China. The Government of the Republic of
Singapore recognizes the Government of the People's Republic of
China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
