<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Infamous Military Agency Dissolved in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The ceremony for the Bakorstanas closure was held in the
Indonesian Military (TNI) headquarters in East Jakarta Monday. It
was a followup of the presidential decree issued on March 10, 2000.
President Abdurrahman Wahid ordered the dissolution of the agency
in response to public criticism.
</P>
<P>
Following the official dissolution of the agency, the majority
of the archives compiled by the agency will be destroyed soon.
</P>
<P>
"The larger part of Bakorstanas' database is related to persons
and groups. This (information) will be annihilated because it is
no longer needed," Lt. Gen. Djamari Chaniago, general affairs
chief for the TNI,was quoted by the Jakarta Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
Bakorstanas was established by former president Soeharto in
September 1988 to replace the Operational Command for the
Restoration of Security and Order. The agency was founded to deal
with any perceived problems to the country's stability.
</P>
<P>
The agency screened prospective state officials and also was
reportedly used by Soeharto's New Order administration to silence
government critics and take action against anyone believed to have
links with the banned Indonesian Communist Party. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
