<HEADLINE> hke041107 - Animals Affected by Mayon Eruption Get Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA April 11 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Animal Welfare
Society has assured month-long feeding and "medical mission" on
farm animals affected by the last eruptions of Mt. Mayon,
Philippine News Agency(PNA) said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The week-long eruptions of Mayon volcano later in February had
affected not only humans inhabiting the slopes of the volcano but
also farm animals abounding the area, the PNA said.
</P>
<P>
At least 49 heads of cattle upslope of the village Matanag in
Legazpi city were confirmed to have died from the ultra hot
volcanic materials spawned by the volcano and more have died due
to illness acquired from inhaling ash-laden air.
</P>
<P>
Local agriculture officials earlier reported an over 400 heads
of cows, carabaos and goats suffering from various illnesses and
which had 'lost their appetite' due to massive inhalation of ashes.
</P>
<P>
These aside from those who were seen by farmers as hopeless to
recover and had already been sold at a cheap price. Society
veterinarians who arrived there last week, however,appealed to
farmers to defer plans of selling their sick animals,swearing they
will exhaust all efforts in reviving them. 
</P>
