<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Chamber of Commerce Launches Ads Campaign for China PNTR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The United States Chamber of
Commerce will kick off a pro-trade ad campaign on Tuesday to
prepare for the final showdown on Capitol Hill over normal trade
status with China later this month.
</P>
<P>
The Chamber, in a series of media commercials, will also charge
union leaders of misleading their members and the public about the
importance of free trade.
</P>
<P>
"Our ads point out the truth about trade with China. Free trade
will bring greater opportunity for American workers and farmers.
It will also bring greater opportunity to the Chinese people,"
said Thomas Donohue, Chamber President and CEO.
</P>
<P>
Referring to Union leaders who have planned a Washington rally
against free trade for Wednesday on April 12, Donohue said, "Don't
want to see this happen," since they are pursuing their own
political agenda.
</P>
<P>
Congress is scheduled to vote on whether to extend Permanent
Normal Trade Relations (PNTR) to China in the week of May 22, in
order to benefit from a negotiated trade deal with the country
last November. The Chamber has called the trade deal "critical" to
American interests and urged members of Congress to grant PNTR
when it comes up for a vote.
</P>
<P>
"Let's be clear," Donohue said. "Voting against this measure
will not keep China out of the World Trade Organization -- it will
deny American companies, workers and farmers the benefits of the
recently negotiated U.S.- China trade deal that lowers barriers to
American goods and services."
</P>
<P>
The Chamber's print commercials are scheduled to run in Roll
Call and The Washington Post. Radio ads are also scheduled for
WTOP-AM/FM and the local broadcast of Imus in the Morning.
</P>
<P>
The media effort is part of a larger Chamber initiative to
ensure passage of PNTR for China, which involves 13 field
representatives in congressional districts around the country, and
15 Washington-based lobbyists.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Chamber of Commerce is the world's largest business
federation representing more than three million businesses and
organizations of every size, sector and region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
