<HEADLINE> Town of Dragon Celebrates Week Long Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Puyang City in central China's
Henan Province is holding activities over the next seven days
celebrating the Chinese dragon.
</P>
<P>
Puyang, known as "the town of dragon", is home to three shell-
shaped dragons dating back to over 6,400 years. The dragon designs
are the oldest and most vivid ever discovered in China.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 renowned scholars from at home and abroad will
participate in a seminar on the dragon and the Chinese nation. A
cultural heritage exhibition will be among a series of activities
to be held this week.
</P>
<P>
Puyang will also hold trade talks and a tourism trade fair.
</P>
