<HEADLINE> Shanghai Builds Butterfly Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A butterfly park has been built
in Sheshan Mountain Tourism Zone, east China's Shanghai
Municipality, and will be opened to visitors by mid April this
year.
</P>
<P>
Covering 800 square meters, the Park will become home to more
than 5,000 butterflies.
</P>
<P>
The Park has special glass windows for visitors to watch and
observe the more than 20 species of butterflies.
</P>
<P>
Sheshan Mountain State Tourism Zone, built four years ago, is
30 kilometers away from Shanghai proper. It receives two million
visitors annually. 
