<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Corporate Bond with Floating Interest to be Issued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- China's first corporate bond with
floating interest rate-- the Third Three Gorges Bond-- will be
issued by the first half of this year, according to today's "China
Securities".
</P>
<P>
The three-billion-yuan (about 362 U.S. dollars) bond, with a
maturity of ten years, has an interest rate 1.65-1.75 percentage
points higher than the ruling interest rate, said CITIC Securities,
the managing underwriter of the bond.
</P>
<P>
Interest will be paid each year with principal paid back after
the maturity of the bond.
</P>
<P>
Analysts believed that the new bond will help investors reduce
risks brought by changes in bank interest and will make the
issuance of long-term bonds easier.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
