<HEADLINE> Idle State Equipment to be Traded on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A new official website will
provide trade for idle state-owned equipment and facilities at an
estimated value of "a couple of hundred billion" yuan, according
to "China Business Times".
</P>
<P>
The website--www.china-plant.com--is established by the
Facilities Management Association under the State Development
Planning Commission. It includes 67 kinds of equipment, detailed
information on its database and offers sales, lease, auctions and
services via the Net
</P>
<P>
According to a survey conducted by the association, idle state
assets account for eight percent of total state assets in China
due to construction of redundant projects and recent economic
restructuring.
</P>
<P>
The poor management and maintenance of equipment has incurred
huge waste. Total trade volume of equipment in 1999 stood at a
mere three billion yuan (361 million U.S. dollars) with idle
assets reaching some 20 billion yuan in Shanghai alone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
