<HEADLINE> Rare Species of Shrimp Found in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A rare species of shrimp which
can live in temperatures below freezing was found in Irian Jaya,
Indonesia, according to the Indonesian Observer Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The shrimp species was found by the Irian Jaya chapter of the
World Wildlife Fund (WWF) late last month at Lake Habema in the
Jayawijaya Mountains in Wamena district.
</P>
<P>
"The shrimp looks like a prawn but it is rather thin and can
live in icy rivers under the slopes of the Jayawijaya Mountains.
Prawns cannot live in such conditions," the chapter's head of
marine and beach conservation research M. Putrawidjaya said.
</P>
<P>
He said locals do not eat the unusual shrimps, but instead
serve them to foreign tourists visiting Wamena in the central of
Irian Jaya.
</P>
</TEXT>
