<HEADLINE> Shantou to Step Up Marine Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The coastal city in south China's
Guangdong Province will step up the efforts to develop marine
economy.
</P>
<P>
A recent plan calls for the marine industry to reach more than
15 percent of the city's gross domestic product (GDP) in a decade.
Statistics show that the figure stood at 2.53 billion yuan last
year, accounting for 5.6 percent of Shantou's GDP.
</P>
<P>
Priority will be given to the development of fishery, tourism,
transport and offshore industry, city authorities said. The
construction of basic facilities, including bridges, expressways,
railways and berths will be accelerated.
</P>
<P>
Shantou has a coastal line of 289 kilometers. Its sea area
covers about 10,000 square kilometers, five times the city's land
area.  
