<HEADLINE> Ningxia Tapping Tourism Resources At Mausoleum of Xixia Emperor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A privately-owned enterprise in
northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region will sponsor
tourism projects at the mausoleum of the Xixia Emperor in
cooperation with a Shanghai company to develop local economy
through the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
The project will be jointly funded by the Ningxia Sanxin
Technological Development Co. Ltd and the Social Undertaking
Investment Business Company of the Shanghai Pudong Development
Group. Involving a total investment of 200 million yuan, the
project will be completed in five years.
</P>
<P>
The tourism project will center on the development of scenic
spots around the mausoleum of the Xixia Emperor in the eastern
part of the Mount Helan.
</P>
<P>
The mausoleum, 30 kilometers west of Yinchuan, covers an area
of 50 square kilometers. The mausoleum has been under state
protection since 1988.
</P>
<P>
The Kingdom of Xixia was established in the 11th century by a
number of ethnic groups in what is now Ningxia.  
</P>
