<HEADLINE> Chinese Peasant Paintings On-line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 11 (Xinhua) -- With a computer at home, Pan
Xiaoling, a painter in Huxian County in northwest China's Shaanxi
Province, his painting are now accessible on the Net.
</P>
<P>
Since 1950s, farmers in the county created a special painting
school featuring farmer's daily life, evolved from paper cutting,
cross-stitch work and mud sculpture.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 40 years, more than 8,000 such painting works
have been on display during exhibitions in over 60 countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
To let more people overseas know about paintings by local
farmers, Pan bought a computer to provide information on the art
style and latest works for foreign painting fans.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of overseas Internet users have showed interest in
Pan and other peasant artists' painting after browsing Pan's
website.  
</P>
