<HEADLINE> Xi'an Uses Overseas Funds to Develop Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Direct overseas investments and
foreign loans have played an important role in the economic
development of Xi'an, capital of northwest China's Shaanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
According to the municipal planning commission, Xi'an has drawn
a total of 4.44 billion U.S. dollars in direct overseas investment
by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Last year alone, Xi'an used 146 million U.S. dollars of
overseas funds, 29.56 percent of the city's fiscal revenues.
</P>
<P>
The top five investors in the city are from Hong Kong, Japan,
the United States, Taiwan and Britain.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an has also used foreign loans to develop its economy. By
the end of last year, Xi'an approved 229 million dollars of
foreign loans.
</P>
<P>
Loans have come from 11 foreign countries with Japan topping
the list and they were mainly used for urban infrastructure
construction including water and gas supply, telecommunications
and sewage treatment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
