<HEADLINE> East Chinese Bonded Zone Draws More Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A bonded Zone in Ningbo, in east
China's Zhejiang Province, drew 54.48 million US dollars of
contractual foreign investment in the first quarter of this year,
up 163 percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
The Zone actually utilized 19.3 million US dollars of foreign
funds, up 60 percent. Among the Zone's new foreign-funded projects,
the number of high-tech enterprises, Taiwan-funded businesses, and
processing trade projects has increased by a huge margin. Five of
the projects has more than ten million US dollars in investments
each.
</P>
