<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Island Province to Ban "White Pollution" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 11 (Xinhua) -- China's island province of Hainan
has formally stopped approving new production line of foam plastic
dishware and urged producers to build recycle system to reduce "
white pollution".
</P>
<P>
All dishware producers are required to build proper recycle
system within one year and have been requested to increase the
production of degradable plastics.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government will ban the use of plastic bags
thinner than 0.025 mm from May 1.
</P>
<P>
Bins with special signs to collect plastic dishware and bag
will be added in public places such as the airports, tourist spots
and residential zones.
</P>
<P>
The government hopes the efforts will help increase the
recycling of plastics to 95 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
