<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rising Prices Drive Domestic Tourists Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey in "China Youth
Daily" by the National Tourism Administration showed that a large
number of tourists preferred trips abroad to traveling at home.
</P>
<P>
The Administration attributed the change to price hikes in
several domestic tourist resorts during the lunar new year
holidays, which made domestic travel even more expensive than
trips abroad.
</P>
<P>
Trips to Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand and Vietnam became
attractive to Chinese tourists thanks to the comparatively low
charges.
</P>
<P>
Many tourist cities including Guilin, in the south Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region, and Sanya, in Hainan province increased
accommodation prices as well as admission fees to resort areas
during the Spring Festival.
</P>
<P>
Analysts pointed out that the average consumption level of
Chinese citizens is quite low although more and more people are
making short-term trips during long holidays. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
