<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cultural Corridor To Be Built At Three Gorges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A cultural corridor will be
built along the Three Gorges of the Yangtze River within 10 years.
</P>
<P>
The 193-km-long Three Gorges, in an area between Chongqing
Municipality and central China's Hubei Province, is a well-known
scenic spot in China. The area holds 1,282 archeological sites
including ancient tombs, unique bridges and famous stone carvings.
The most brilliant sites comprise a 2.8-billion-year-old rock and
1.4-million-year-old palaeoanthropological ruins.
</P>
<P>
The cultural corridor will be divided into ten parts,
respectively featuring stone carvings, Sichuan culture, war-theme
culture and etc.
</P>
<P>
Seven key cultural architectures to be built according to the
development program include the Chongqing Theater, Three Gorges
Museum, a library and an art gallery.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000411.0391 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fuzhou to Host International Investment Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Fuzhou, the capital city of east
China's Fujian Province will host its annual international trade
and investment fair in May.
</P>
<P>
The month-long 2000 Fuzhou International Trade and Investment
Fair will provide a total of 319 potential investment projects
worth 10.48 billion U.S. dollars, according to a press conference
held recently in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
This year's fair, the seventh of its kind, coincides with a
series of economic and technological exchange activities including
the Cross-Straits High-tech Development Fair, investment and trade
seminars, mayors' forum, tourism promotion program and Internet
investment projects.
</P>
<P>
A senior local official said that since the city initiated the
first trade and investment fair in 1994, the annual event has
become a major venue for Fuzhou in attracting overseas capital and
creating business opportunities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
