<DOCNO> XIE20000411.0394 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanxi to Build Highway to Water Fall on Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 11 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi Province
will spend 100 million yuan (12 million U.S. dollars) to build a
37.5 km long highway linking the most famous waterfall on the
Yellow River with Jixian County.
</P>
<P>
Located 46 km away from the county, the Hukou Waterfall has
become the a renowned tourism site, attracting flocks of domestic
and overseas tourists every year. The waterfall is in a narrow,
precipitous gorge and is known for the rapid speed of the water
and its thunderous sound.
</P>
<P>
But the road to the waterfall zigzagging across mountainous
areas is shabby and dangerous, said a local tourism official. This
has caused many traffic difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The planned highway will shorten driving from Jixian to Hukou
to 30 minutes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000411.0395 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing to Become Aviation Hub in Western China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing Municipality in
southwest China will become the largest aviation hub in western
region with the expansion of the Jiangbei International Airport
and the construction of two new airports.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the 370-million yuan Wanzhouwuqiao Airport has
already started and the airport is expected to begin operation in
2003.
</P>
<P>
The Jiangbei International Airport was built in 1990
accommodating one million passengers a year. In 1999, the Airport
handled 2.4 million passengers.
</P>
<P>
Renovations began last year and is expected to be completed by
May 2000. A total of 1.7 billion yuan will be spent to improve the
Airport's facilities.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion, the Airport will be capable of handling 60,000
landings and take-offs, 8 million passengers and 200,000 tons of
cargo per year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
