<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuban FM Demands Solidarity Defense </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 11 (Xinhua)-- Cuban Foreign Minister Felipe Perez
Roque said Tuesday that Southern Summit must establish the demand
of the solidarity for developing countries but not the
globalization of injustice.
</P>
<P>
The minister spoke at the opening session of the Group of 77's
foreign ministers meeting taking place in Havana the day before
the South Summit to start Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
 He also expressed that Cuba backs up the reform and
democratizing of United Nations Organization.
</P>
<P>
 Roques also showed in favor of sovereignty and sovereign
equality of nations, non-intervention and a peaceful solution to
disputes.
</P>
<P>
Perez Roque described as evident violation of the principals of
the UN Charter the so-called humanitarian intervention right
certain powerful countries intend to impose and requested for the
Group of 77 to oppose this kind of intervention.
</P>
<P>
 The Southern Summit will examine the globalization of world
economy, which cannot keep on meaning underdevelopment, poverty
and exclusion for majorities and luxurious and unnecessary
squandering for a privileged minority, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We've the right to dream for a future world for our children
better than that we've lived in", said this Foreign Minister, who
called for the unity of countries on the way to development.
</P>
</TEXT>
