<HEADLINE> Toronto Unveils Logo in Bid for 2008 Olympic Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Canada's biggest city Toronto
unveiled its official logo and Internet site Tuesday in its bid
for 2008 Olympic games.
</P>
<P>
The logo features a red fireworks-style maple leaf to represent
the Olympics in Canadian culture, according to a local press
release.
</P>
<P>
The logo acts as a bridge to TO-2008.com, the newly opened
Internet site for information of Toronto's bid for the 2008
Olympic games.
</P>
<P>
Toronto is one of the 10 cities in the world bidding for the
2008 Summer Games. The International Olympic Committee is expected
to announce the successful applicant in Moscow in July 2001.
</P>
