<HEADLINE> British Envoys to Travel to Syria Over Mideast Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Britain said on Tuesday that two
senior British envoys are scheduled to visit Syria in the next few
weeks to do Britain's efforts to revive prospects for Israeli-
Syrian peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Tony Blair's envoy Lord Levy will travel to
Syria later in April and Foreign Office Minister Peter Hain is due
in Damascus in mid-May, a Foreign Office official told reporters.
</P>
<P>
The official said the visits were a sign of the "need to go out
there and do our best to help get the peace process back on the
rails".
</P>
