<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Africa Air Consultative Meeting Opens in Ghana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 11 (Xinhua) -- An informal consultative meeting to
discuss air traffic rights between Francophone and Anglophone
states in west Africa opened in Ghana's capital Accra Tuesday,
reported Ghana News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from Ghana, Nigeria, Guinea and Gambia attended the
two-day meeting to discuss the ratification and implementation of
the Yamoussoukro Declaration, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The Yamoussoukro Declaration, adopted last year in
Yamoussoukro, capital of Cote d'Ivoire, aimed at harmonizing the
operations of the Yaounde Treaty and the Banjul Accord, signed
respectively by the Francophone west African states and their
Anglophone counterparts.
</P>
<P>
The Yamoussoukro Declaration would enable African airlines to
operate liberally within members' airspace through co-operation,
it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
