<HEADLINE> Peru Underscores Convergence Between Non-Aligned, G-77 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jose Urrutia, who represents Foreign Minister,Fernando de
Trazegnies, in the South Summit's ministerial meeting, said that
both organizations have as their main task to promote the joint
solution of common problems.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the local press, the Peruvian diplomat
said that Non-Aligned countries ministerial meeting, which took
place in its headquarters at Cartagena, Colombia, supports the
present meeting.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need to find ways of action to satisfy the
access to markets and advanced technology, and to participate in
the decision-making in finance.
</P>
<P>
He said that the countries of the South must convince
industrialized countries on the importance of a more just sharing
of wealth.
</P>
<P>
Over 60 heads of state are assisting at the G-77 South Summit.
</P>
<P>
The current summit is the first ever summit and the largest
gathering in the history of the Group of 77. 
</P>
