<HEADLINE> 5.1 Quake Hits South Mexico Coasts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A 5.1 degree earthquake on
the Richter scale was registered at 13:35 o'clock Tuesday on
Mexican coasts of Guerrero and Michoacan states. Up to now it isn'
t known if there are victims or material damages.
</P>
<P>
National Seismological Service (SSN) said on Tuesday that it's
mindful of possible repercussions that could come from this
phenomenon in this area, south of Mexico's capital.
</P>
<P>
At the same time Geophysical Institute's organism of National
Autonomous University of Mexico (UNAM), made it known the quake
was detected 17.67 degrees northern latitude and less than 102. 92
western longitude.  
</P>
