<HEADLINE> Poverty Is Political Instability Factor: Nigerian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian President Olusegun
Obasanjo said Tuesday at this Cuban capital that poverty is a
source of political distress and civil armed conflicts, during a
press conference at the South Summit.
</P>
<P>
Developed countries should cancel foreign debts of Third World
countries, which cannot be demanded to pay but risking the loss of
their democratic govern ability, said the president.
</P>
<P>
Obasanjo, whose country heads the Presidency of the Group of 77
(G-77), which is celebrating its first great meeting at Havana,
reminded that wars taking place nowadays in Africa, have a
historical and structural origin.
</P>
<P>
These nations, he said, must not relinquish their claim before
United Nations, the Paris Club, the International Monetary Fund (
IMF), the World Bank (WB), to eliminate such compromises that
affect the economic and social development of peoples.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the Havana meeting, he said that the setting up of
some sort of follow up mechanism for the accords agreed upon is
being discussed here.
</P>
</TEXT>
