<HEADLINE> Putin To Visit Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 11 (Xinhua)-- Russian President Vladimir Putin
will make an official visit to the United Kingdom on coming Sunday,
a spokesman for Downing Street said.
</P>
<P>
Putin is expected to fly into London late on Sunday night for
talks with Prime Minister Tony Blair.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also confirmed that Britain was "still under
active discussion" with Russia on a possible meeting between Putin
and Queen Elizabeth II.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the visit, the spokesman for Blair said that it would
cement a "new strategic relationship" between the two countries
and added that Putin was expected to return to Moscow on Monday
evening,rather than go on to visit other Western capitals.
</P>
<P>
Putin and Blair first met for informal talks in Putin's home
town of St Petersburg shortly before he was elected president on
March 26.
</P>
<P>
Putin had previously said that he would not be travelling
abroad until he appoints a prime minister, a role he is currently
holding.
</P>
<P>
He is scheduled to appoint a prime minister after his May 7
inauguration.
</P>
<P>
Russia has faced condemnation from human rights groups in
Britain over its actions in the breakaway republic of Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
Downing Street said that Blair would express his concern about
the situation in Chechnya and press for greater access for
international organizations.
</P>
<P>
"We will express, as we did in St Petersburg, our concerns,"
said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"But equally we believe the best way to express those concerns
is engagement rather than isolation," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
